{
  "texts": [
    "NFs performs a series of invertible transformations on the simple prior distribution to model the complicated target distribution [211].",
    "In addition, these transformations can be facilitated via the invertible neural networks with the learnable parameters.",
    "By sampling from the learned complicated distribution, NFs can generate the new samples similar to the training samples.• Variational autoencoders (VAEs).",
    "VAEs consist of an encoder and a decoder [212].",
    "The encoder transforms the input samples to a series of parameters in the latent space to generate the latent variables."
  ]
}